  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "We have CI tests running on K8s 1.6.1 (stated via kubeadm) , and the tests fail because they cannot create filesystem or object store.  Here is a snippet of from the rook-api log\r\n\r\n`2017-04-25 17:33:30.925102 E | api: failed to start mds: failed to create mds keyring. failed to get mds secrets. User \"system:serviceaccount:rook:default\" cannot get secrets in the namespace \"rook\". (get secrets mds)\r\n2017-04-25 17:33:30.925141 I | api: a6696802-38d1-446a-9bd3-d734d7b95881\tPOST\t/filesystem\tCreateFileSystem\t500 Internal Server Error\t1.595739846s`\r\n\r\nand \r\n\r\n`2017-04-25 17:33:03.521854 I | api: 9496f380-28ff-455e-8b0f-8c9e1bc5b79d\tPOST\t/objectstore\tCreateObjectStore\t(start)\r\n2017-04-25 17:33:03.521884 I | api-k8s: Starting the Object store\r\n2017-04-25 17:33:03.521909 I | op-rgw: start running rgw\r\n2017-04-25 17:33:03.550823 E | api: failed to create object store: failed to start rgw. failed to create rgw keyring. failed to get rgw secrets. User \"system:serviceaccount:rook:default\" cannot get secrets in the namespace \"rook\". (get secrets rgw)\r\n2017-04-25 17:33:03.550866 I | api: 9496f380-28ff-455e-8b0f-8c9e1bc5b79d\tPOST\t/objectstore\tCreateObjectStore\t500 Internal Server Error\t29.021304ms`\r\n\r\nEnvironment : K8s (started via KubeAdm)\r\n\r\nRepro Steps :\r\n1. Start k8s 1.6 via Kubeamd (https://kubernetes.io/docs/getting-started-guides/kubeadm/)\r\n2. Start rook operator, cluster and client\r\n3. Create a file system and object store\r\n\r\nExpected result : File system and object store created successfully and mds and rgw services started\r\n\r\nActual Result : File system and object store not created, mds and rgw services not started. ",
